            <article>
                <h2>Welcome to Your AI Skills Development Programme</h2>
                
                <p>This semester-long programme is designed to help you develop essential AI skills for your sport science studies and future career. You will work through these materials at your own pace, building competencies that align with Birmingham Newman University's 6-level AI framework.</p>

                <div class="info-box">
                    <strong>How This Programme Works:</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Attend the 2-hour introduction session to get started</li>
                        <li>Choose your pathway based on your current AI experience</li>
                        <li>Work through modules at your own pace throughout the semester</li>
                        <li>Apply your skills to your actual assessments (SPU412, SPU514, and others)</li>
                        <li>Track your progress and revisit modules as needed</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <h2>Understanding the 6-Level AI Framework</h2>
                
                <p>Birmingham Newman University uses a 6-level framework to define appropriate AI use in assessments. Understanding this framework is essential for using AI correctly and avoiding academic misconduct.</p>

                <div class="level-framework">
                    <div class="level-grid">
                        <div class="level-box">
                            <h4>Level 1: No AI</h4>
                            <p>Assessment completed entirely without AI assistance.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="level-box">
                            <h4>Level 2: Idea Generation</h4>
                            <p>AI for brainstorming and structuring. No AI content in final submission.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="level-box">
                            <h4>Level 3: Editing</h4>
                            <p>AI for clarity improvements. Original work required in appendix.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="level-box">
                            <h4>Level 4: Task Completion</h4>
                            <p>AI completes tasks. You evaluate and discuss outputs. Cite AI use.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="level-box">
                            <h4>Level 5: Collaboration</h4>
                            <p>AI as co-pilot throughout. No need to specify AI content.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="level-box">
                            <h4>Level 6: Mandatory AI</h4>
                            <p>Must use AI and document how you used and refined outputs.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <p style="text-align: center; margin-top: 15px;">
                        <strong><a href="framework.html" style="color: #3498db;">Learn more about the 6-level framework →</a></strong>
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="warning-box">
                    <strong>⚠️ Important:</strong> Different assessments require different AI levels. Always check your assessment brief before using AI. Using AI inappropriately can constitute academic misconduct.
                </div>

                <h2>Choose Your Pathway</h2>
                
                <p>Select the pathway that matches your current AI experience and confidence. You can switch pathways at any time if you find one too easy or too challenging.</p>

                <div class="pathway-grid">
                    <a href="foundation.html" class="pathway-card foundation">
                        <h3>Foundation</h3>
                        <p><strong>New to AI?</strong></p>
                        <p>Learn the basics, understand Levels 1-3, and build confidence with essential tools.</p>
                        <p style="margin-top: 15px; font-size: 0.9rem;">→ Start here if you have minimal AI experience</p>
                    </a>

                    <a href="development.html" class="pathway-card development">
                        <h3>Development</h3>
                        <p><strong>Some experience?</strong></p>
                        <p>Master Levels 3-4, develop critical evaluation skills, and prepare for SPU412.</p>
                        <p style="margin-top: 15px; font-size: 0.9rem;">→ Start here if you have used AI before</p>
                    </a>

                    <a href="advanced.html" class="pathway-card advanced">
                        <h3>Advanced</h3>
                        <p><strong>Confident user?</strong></p>
                        <p>Focus on Levels 4-5, research skills, and SPU514 preparation.</p>
                        <p style="margin-top: 15px; font-size: 0.9rem;">→ Start here if you use AI regularly</p>
                    </a>

                    <a href="expert.html" class="pathway-card expert">
                        <h3>Expert</h3>
                        <p><strong>Advanced skills?</strong></p>
                        <p>Master Level 6, dissertation support, and sophisticated research workflows.</p>
                        <p style="margin-top: 15px; font-size: 0.9rem;">→ Start here for Level 6 and dissertation</p>
                    </a>
                </div>

                <h2>Assessment-Specific Support</h2>
                
                <p>Need help with a specific assignment? These guides provide targeted support for common sport science assessments:</p>

                <div class="assessment-links">
